From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nitin Kamboj <nitin.kamboj@amd.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] gst-plugins-base: AI layout video formats, tensor fixes,
 FORMATS_ALL macro integration, planar RGB naming cleanup (squashed)

Squashed working-tree delta against subprojects/gst-plugins-base/ covering
four logical parts. Apply from the subprojects/gst-plugins-base/ directory
with `git am` or `patch -p1`.

Part 1 -- Add AI layout formats (AMD VAI inference IP)
  Registers GstVideoFormat enum entries, pack/unpack routines, formats[]
  table rows, and GstVideoScaleFormat mappings for the custom tensor
  formats produced by the AMD AI Layout Formatter IP. Formats: C4/C8
  RGBA/RGBX variants (8-bit, BF16, FP16, FLOAT), BGR/BGRA packed and
  planar variants, BGRx variants, RGB/RGBP variants, and GRAY BF16/FP16/
  FLOAT.

Part 2 -- AI tensor correctness fixes
  (see prior unified patch; all nine items retained)

Part 3 -- GST_VIDEO_FORMATS_ALL macro integration
  Appends every registered AI layout format name to both BIG_ENDIAN and
  LITTLE_ENDIAN branches of GST_VIDEO_FORMATS_ALL in video-format.h so
  videoconvert/videoscale/videotestsrc/compositor pad templates and
  gst_video_formats_raw() see the full enum.

Part 4 -- Planar RGB naming cleanup and RGBA8P symmetry
  1. Rename RGBP_BF16/RGBP_FP16/RGBP_FLOAT to RGB_BF16P/RGB_FP16P/
     RGB_FLOATP, matching the existing BGR planar convention
     ({base}{type}P). Format strings become rgb_bf16p / rgb_fp16p /
     rgb_floatp.
  2. Fix video-format.h BGR_FP16P slot that wrongly repeated
     GST_VIDEO_FORMAT_BGR_BF16P.
  3. Add GST_VIDEO_FORMAT_RGBA8P as the R-first planar counterpart to
     BGRA8P (PLANE0123 vs PLANE2103), with matching pack/unpack,
     formats[] row, GST_VIDEO_FORMATS_ALL entries, and video-info.c /
     video-converter.c parity.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Nitin Kamboj <nitin.kamboj@amd.com>
